CAN Bus Tutorial and Resources

This repository contains information and tutorials for working with the CAN bus using Arduino, along with a datasheet for a 3.3KW charger.

Protocol

When the data is retrieved it will dump it into the following HEX format. ID, BIT1, BIT2, BIT3, BIT4, BIT5, BIT6, BIT7, BIT8 The ID usually represents a Node within your vehicle. Let’s make a simple example. (The below is made up and not real, just an example) Air Conditioning Node ID= 0x402 TURN AIRCON OFF = 13 TURN AIRCON ON = 14 SET AIRCON BLOWER TO LOW = 7C SET AIRCON BLOWER TO MEDIUM 8C SET AIRCON BLOWER TO HIGH 9C So if we turn on the Aircon and set it on medium the message will look like this 0x402, 13, 8C the same goes for other nodes, example Central Locking Central Locking ID= 0x503 LOCK all doors = 14 So if you press the button to lock all doors the message will look like this 0x502, 14 You can try the following messages. Load the send examples from the Arduino examples menu and change were relevant. Engage Rear Locker.: CAN.sendMsgBuf(0x2B0, 0, 4 ,stmp); Left Blinker On: CAN.sendMsgBuf(0x2A8, 0, 6 ,stmp); Right Blinker On: CAN.sendMsgBuf(0x2A8, 0, 6 ,stmp); ESP On/OFF: CAN.sendMsgBuf(0x2B0, 0, 4 ,stmp);
